e. If Foo.class is missing, the JVM might fail to find it, leading to issues with loading. While I'm considering options for improving coverage, we need solid high-coverage integration testing as a priority too!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering native execution**\\n\\nI’m feeling uncertain about the native execution. It seems I could either accept success or rely on defineClass, but I can’t just guard against native. I’m thinking I can assert that at least one run occurs with zero errors. Ignoring failure counts feels weak because it could hide broken behavior. Maybe we need to ensure tests run natively? A failing JUnit assertion doesn’t help.\\n\\nIt’s interesting that Native Image with `-H:Preserve` might work for classes, but regular tests may not have that. I wonder if we can create a small local Java main for deeper testing, but I need to consider time and additional metadata for `ClassloaderChangeTest`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating native support**\\n\\nIt doesn't feel relevant right now, but I need to dig into the native support. GraalVM Native Image potentially supports `ClassLoader#defineClass`, but I wonder if it can really load classes at runtime. Since the native image operates in a closed world, it seems unlikely. If `defineClass` could define new classes, it likely wouldn’t run any compiled code, leading to an UnsupportedFeatureError. I’m considering that while reports with Preserve might work with \\\"Class.getDeclaredMethods,\\\" it appears that the code in class bytes isn't being compiled, so JIT won’t happen.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_oIxgxARMz9At3A0C6OZMbCeC|fc_0d0c86e768bfaeaa0169ef777a5af881a3a33474faa64bec8d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); cat > \"$tmp/Foo.java\" <<'EOF'\npublic class Foo {\n    public String doIt() {\n        return \"Hello From Foo\";\n    }\n}\nEOF\njavac --release 8 \"$tmp/Foo.java\"\nbase64 -w0 \"$tmp/Foo.class\"\nrm -rf \"$tmp\"", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 310, "output": 1859, "cacheRead": 23552, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25721, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777301344343, "responseId": "resp_0d0c86e768bfaeaa0169ef7760d46081a3801246718f734305"}}
